column30:
I am Hasnat Ayub Khan, a Master of Science in Biotechnology candidate at COMSATS University Islamabad, Abbottabad Campus, graduating in Spring 2025. Since 2013, I have managed a 10-acre family farm specializing in wheat and maize. As a government registered farmer, I have faced challenges with quality seeds, fertilizers, and machinery, prompting me to seek sustainable alternatives.
During my bachelor's, I researched at the Biofuel and Bioproduct Lab, focusing on Waste to Worth, Zero Waste, and the Circular Economy. I developed an integrated system combining crop cultivation with waste recycling, including mushroom cultivation, biomaterial and bioleather production, anaerobic digestion, composting, and wastewater treatment.
I have conducted experiments transforming crop and campus waste into valuable products, producing biogas for cooking, heating, and electricity. Certified in vermicomposting, I founded Seedling (SMC-Private) Limited, promoting organic farming, vermicompost production, mushroom cultivation, and biogas plant installation for a sustainable agricultural future.

column49: Upgrade offers an innovative solution for job search and recruitment by providing a user-friendly platform that connects job seekers with employers in the Tajik market. Upgrade offers a one-stop solution for job seekers and employers, making the recruitment process faster, easier and more efficient. The platform offers a variety of features for job seekers such as: the ability to search for job openings across different industries and locations, the ability to create a professional profile highlighting qualifications, experience, and skills, the ability to apply to multiple job postings in a single click, and access to career development resources. On the employer side, the platform offers features such as: the ability to post job listings, search resumes, communicate with potential hires, track recruitment process and make data-driven decisions. Upgrade aims to make the recruitment process more efficient and effective for both job seekers and employers in the Tajik market.
column50: Upgrade stands out from other job search and recruitment platforms in the Tajik market by offering a unique combination of features and services tailored to the local market, a user-friendly interface, a comprehensive one-stop solution for job seekers and employers, career development resources for job seekers, and data-driven decision making tools for employers. Additionally, Upgrade will have the first available database of verified resumes and jobs in the country, ensuring that both job seekers and employers have access to high-quality and reliable information, this will make the recruitment process more efficient and effective. It makes Upgrade a competitive alternative in the market.
column51: As a startup, we are currently in the MVP stage of our product development. We have been testing and refining our job search and recruitment platform, Upgrade, to ensure that it meets the needs of the Tajik market. During this period, our total revenue has been limited, as we have not yet implemented a monetization model. The revenue for the past 12 months is less than $200. While we are still in the development phase, we are focused on perfecting our product before introducing it to the market.
column53: As a startup, we have been working diligently on building a comprehensive and innovative job search and recruitment platform, Upgrade. While it's true that the MVP phase is an essential step in the development process, it also comes with its own set of expenses. Our expenses over the past 12 months have exceeded $5,000, which were spent on various services to support and improve our platform, such as website development, security measures and hosting fees. But we also spent money on other services such as legal, marketing, and employee salaries which are essential for the growth and success of our startup. All these expenses were worth it as they will help us to bring a better product to the market.

column7: InsuTank is a water tank manufacturing company which aims to disrupt how water is stored in overhead water tanks in Pakistan by its unique design. More than 90% of households in Paksitan use plastic water tanks for storage which do not come with any kind of insulation or weather protection resulting in excessively cold water in winters and burning hot in summers. InsuTank due to its embedded insulation, ensures more than 30% electricity and water savings in summers and upto 40% energy savings in cold weather.  Currently, online B2C model is being expedited however, B2B as well as franchising model is under planning for near future.

column49: The Electronic Health Record (EHR) system offers several innovative solutions for the healthcare system in Tajikistan:  Improved data collection and management: EHRs allow for the digitization of patient information, which can help improve the accuracy and completeness of patient data.  Enhanced communication and collaboration: EHRs allow healthcare providers to easily share patient information, which can improve coordination of care and reduce errors.  Increased efficiency and productivity: EHRs can automate many tasks, such as appointment scheduling, lab test ordering, and tracking patient progress, which can help improve healthcare providers' productivity.  Improved patient outcomes: EHRs can help improve patient outcomes by providing healthcare providers with more accurate and complete patient information, which can lead to better diagnosis and treatment.  Improved patient engagement: EHRs allow patients to access their medical records, communicate with their doctors, and monitor their progress, which can empower them to take an active role in their care.  Advanced analytics: EHRs allow for advanced analytics tools to be used to extract insights from patient data, that can be used for research, population health management, and also be used for making decisions for the betterment of the patient's health.  Better access to care: EHRs enable healthcare providers to access patient information from anywhere, which can help improve access to care for patients in rural or remote areas.  Compliance with international regulations: EHRs can help medical facilities in Tajikistan to comply with international regulations and standards for healthcare data management and privacy.
column50: The healthcare system in Tajikistan is currently facing the challenge of a fragmented electronic health record (EHR) system, where various clinics have their own EHR databases that operate independently. Our aim is to bridge this gap by developing a centralized EHR database that covers the entire country. This innovative solution will enable healthcare providers to access patient information across the entire healthcare system, leading to improved patient care, increased efficiency and better coordination of care

column7: Fuel Station is the world’s first digital marketplace for all types of fuels (gas, petrol, propane) to business clients on their doorsteps. column30: I have been an English tutor since 2009. In 2018, I released a web-platform to teach English online through real time communication. I had around 30 students. I was happy to make a decent living while working online.  In 2020, the platform became popular in the local community because of the lockdown. I hired 20 female teachers and attracted more than 300 students. However, it was because of the increased popularity that the financial success of the project came at doubt. I earned more but I had to spend 99 percent of the revenue. The inflow of students and the constant aspiration to keep the quality of education at high level created big operational expenses: teachers’ training, constant quality monitoring, and technical support. However, the biggest problem was when after gaining enough training and experience the teachers would want to work independently. Round after round, I had to invest time, energy, and money in new teachers only to see how they leave the company. The project was not profitable. I closed it and took a break to rethink the sustainability strategy. I spent next year doing research and came to understand the other side: the teachers.  In 2022, I applied to Accelerator Prosperity and won a $ 10.000 USD investment with the idea of de-centralized learning platform where each teacher can work independently and get evaluated by his or her students. The platform enables a teacher to build a valid reputation by collecting votes from students.

column49: Leontev and Partners is a place where a student and a teacher can reach high results without intermediaries. We advocate for de-centralized quality management in language tutoring.  Traditionally, the administration of language courses controls the education process by creating a long chain of managers responsible for the quality of education. Their job titles include methodologist, content-managers, supervisors, coordinators, curators etc. At a certain point, a teacher comes to understand that it is better to work with the students without intermediaries and leaves a company. column49: InstaWorld offers an innovative solution for e-commerce vendors by providing a data-driven, intelligent, and automated delivery service platform. Our proprietary software uses deep analytics to dynamically assign orders to logistics partners for optimum fulfilment and delivery, enables data-driven cash advances, and tracks all activities in real-time via APIs.  One of the unique features of our platform is the ability to provide advance cash on delivery payments to merchants. This feature is particularly beneficial for e-commerce vendors as it eases their cash flow issues and helps them grow faster. We are the only company providing this service, and as a digital company, we have access to data which allows us to extend this advance with minimal risk exposure.  Our technology stack includes the use of Django (python) framework for the backend, Django REST framework for APIs, and React.js for the front-end. This allows for seamless integration with leading e-commerce platforms like Shopify, Woo-commerce, Magento etc, via APIs. Our platform provides real-time tracking of all activities using APIs, and full-visibility into customers online business operations enables advance cash-on-delivery payments at least risk exposure. The platform also allows customers to seamlessly integrate their websites with InstaWorld in minutes, making it easy and convenient for them to use our services.
column50: InstaWorld stands out from other competitors in the market by digitizing the complete value chain through our software. Our fintech-enabled logistics platform seamlessly connects with the sellers' websites and logistics companies via APIs, enabling several unique features. Firstly, by aggregating the orders on a single platform, we are able to lock the cheapest rates with all courier companies, enabling us to offer the best market rates to our customers (online sellers), leading to higher margins for them.  Additionally, our platform offers hassle-free on-boarding within minutes. Our instant service enablement of any logistics company requires no need to sign up individually with any company. All orders can be tracked within a single dashboard, making it easy for customers to manage their deliveries. Our software uses deep analytics and AI-powered algorithms to dynamically route orders to logistics companies for the most optimum delivery timelines, leading to low cancellation rates. This also enables us to distribute sellers' inventory across a network of partner fulfilment centers. Orders are assigned to the nearest location to the consignee resulting in faster fulfilment and cheaper delivery cost.  Furthermore, our API enabled software leverages sales data from customer websites and delivery KPIs data from logistics dashboard to enable us to offer cash advances to sellers with minimal risk exposure, from daily GMV up to 14-days GMV advance. This helps to maintain optimum inventory levels and opens up additional capital for digital ad spend, leading to business growth. Lastly, we use multiple logistic partners always, so we never choke on capacity.  On top of the above-mentioned features, our product also boasts a superior technology stack that allows us to offer better business models for ourselves and our clients. This includes our ability to scale based on volumes and offer more competitive pricing as a result.

column49: The Metric product suite is highly innovative, using various types of technologies to provide a full-service accounting platform to a greatly underserved target audience. The team has been working not only to provide tech features that make financial management easier, but also to create an ecosystem around the product suite that allows for knowledge transfer. Features and technological innovation is explained in more detail in the next question.
column50: Real-time insights and metric tracking: Even businesses that have an accountant struggle to use their own data for decision-making because financial reporting is cyclical and massively delayed. Also, most SME founders neither know the importance of, nor know how to compute or track, their business metrics. Both these issues are solved by Metric, where critical metrics are being calculated and tracked for businesses automatically and in real-time, allowing for immediate decision-making that helps businesses grow.  Simplicity of input: The aim has always been to make Metric the world’s most founder-friendly business finance app, and for this to happen it is critical that the input of transaction data is as simple as possible. For this, the team is constantly working on various integrations (banks, Shopify, POS systems, etc) so that the founder has to do less effort and even less knowledge or skills are required.  Digital Vouchers: Founders that use Metric are able to upload photos of their receipts and invoices, thereby creating digital vouchers for record keeping. Invoices can also be sent to vendors or clients digitally, decreasing the use of paper, and contributing to the environment.  One Picture Accounting ™: Metric uses AI/ML-based tech to offer One Picture Accounting ™ - a feature that allows business owners to simply take photos of their receipts or invoices, and their accounting is done! Not only are these invoices/receipts saved as digital vouchers, our tech also reads these images and logs relevant information into the company’s accounts. This makes accounting extremely simple as well as fast, allowing for a lot more financial inclusion (people who are unable to perhaps add input manually due to lack of knowledge), and saves the entrepreneurs’ time. Metric’s CTO is a Ph.D. in AI/ML and has been working on projects around this all her career.  Sectoral insights: A massive issue in Pakistan and other emerging markets is the lack of real data, especially secondary data, which makes business decision-making extremely difficult. Because businesses are inputting their transaction data into Metric, while the Metric team (or anyone else) has no line of sight to individual data (company privacy is maintained fully), the layer that Metric will build on top is business insights based on anonymized sectoral data. For example, a business selling cakes in Karachi can be told what the average order value of similar businesses in similar regions is, or what the average customer acquisition cost for that sector is. This will allow businesses to make better decisions, and grow faster.  Educational elements: Metric’s founders and team understand that especially in emerging markets such as Pakistan financial education is as critical as a financial product itself. To this end, there are already educational pieces built into the app. For example, anywhere in the app where there is a typical accounting or financial term, this term can be clicked, and a video pops up where the term is explained, and the relevance of the term/metric for the business is also explained. Over time, these videos will be expanded, and more languages will also be added. A “CEO Club” will also be integrated, which will be a forum where entrepreneurs can ask each other questions, and find solutions to their problems locally through the community.

column49: One of the most spoken languages is one of the most difficult to learn. 200 million Chinese learners have challenges memorizing Chinese characters and speaking with the right pronunciation. We have created a unique CC Chinese learning methodology based on animations with associations to memorize Chinese characters in a few minutes and start speaking basic topics in a few months. In Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan, 874 people learned 12x faster by CC Chinese methodology offline. We saved time and money by up to 50% and about $1,5B for our learners' education costs and helped them successfully enroll in Chinese universities. In 2021, pivoted online to market more than $3B, we developed CC Chinese learning app and launched it in May 2022 in Russian and in December 2022 in English. Now we want to scale in CIS countries and English-speaking countries and help to learn Chinese efficiently and fun globally.
column50: As founders-foreigners, we know all the pain and wishes of foreign Chinese learners. Our creative program and more features based on AR and AI will make us outstanding in the future.
